                <p>Object Oriented Programming -- CSCI 689</p>
                <p>Systems Design and Analysis 1 -- CSCI 567</p>
                <p>Systems Design and Analysis 2 -- CSCi 663</p>
                <p>Web Application Frameworks -- CSCI 680</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <br />
                <h2>Education</h2>
                <br />
                <p>
                    <ul class="educationInfoList">
                        <li><strong>Northern Illinois University</strong></li>
                        <li>Masters of Science in Computer Science  [GPA: 3.5]</li>
                        <li><em>Focuses: System Design & Analysis, Databases</em></li>
                        <li>August 2015 - May 2018</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <br />
                <p>
                    &nbsp; At my time in school I've gained first-hand experience programming and coding
                    in various languages. Doing so has given me a solid foundation to start and a launching point to understand
                    the similarities and differences in languages. More Importantly, it's given me a greater
                    understanding of how to learn new things effectively.
                </p>
                <p>
                    &nbsp; The building blocks of my degree have enabled me to discover and learn the necessary skills to create full stack
                    web applications that utilize backend database servers alongside new and popular web-frameworks. 
